Import Data

golfAnalysis <- tibble(read.csv('~/Downloads/golf/analysis.csv')) |>
  mutate(numRounds = deckPickup + discardPickup) |>
  mutate(winBool = ifelse(agentScores < opponentScores, 1, 0))

Initial Analysis

ggplot(data = golfAnalysis, aes(x = agentInitialSums))+
  geom_histogram(aes(y = after_stat(count/1000)), binwidth = 5, fill = 'blue', boundary = 0)+
  labs(x = 'Sum of Cards in Initial Hand', y = 'Proportion of Games', title = 'Distribution of the sum of cards in original hand')+
  theme_light()

ggplot(data = golfAnalysis, aes(x = numRounds))+
  geom_histogram(aes(y = after_stat(count/1000)), fill = 'orange', boundary = 0, binwidth = 3)+
  labs(x = 'Number of Rounds/Game', y = 'Proportion of Games', title = 'Distribution of the number of rounds per game')+
  theme_light()

actionAnalysis2 <- golfAnalysis |>
  pivot_longer(
    cols = c(deckPickupDiscard, deckPickupSwap, discardPickupSwap),
    names_to = 'action',
    values_to = 'count')

ggplot(actionAnalysis2, aes(x = action, y = count))+
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity', fill = 'purple')+
  labs(x = 'Action', y = 'Count', title = 'Analyzing Overall Turn Actions of the Agent')+
  theme_light()

Imagine the Process

For each game, the player:

-Choose \(N \sim \text{Poisson}(9.7)\)

-Choose \(S \sim \text{Normal}(23, 6.5)\)

-Choose actions from \(A \sim \text{Multinomial}(a | N, S)\)

Let’s see if this makes sense in practice.

shortGame <- golfAnalysis |>
  filter(numRounds < 6) |>
  pivot_longer(
    cols = c(deckPickupDiscard, deckPickupSwap, discardPickupSwap),
    names_to = 'action',
    values_to = 'count')

ggplot(shortGame, aes(x = action, y = count/sum(count)))+
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity', fill = 'darkgreen')+
  labs(title = 'Action distribution for games < 6 rounds', x = 'Action', y = 'Proportion of all actions')+
  theme_light()

longGame <- golfAnalysis |>
  filter(numRounds > 15) |>
    pivot_longer(
    cols = c(deckPickupDiscard, deckPickupSwap, discardPickupSwap),
    names_to = 'action',
    values_to = 'count')

ggplot(longGame, aes(x = action, y = count/sum(count)))+
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity', fill = 'green')+
    labs(title = 'Action distribution for games > 15 rounds', x = 'Action', y = 'Proportion of all actions')+
  theme_light()

medGame1 <- golfAnalysis |>
  filter(numRounds >= 6 & numRounds < 10) |>
  pivot_longer(
    cols = c(deckPickupDiscard, deckPickupSwap, discardPickupSwap),
    names_to = 'action',
    values_to = 'count')

ggplot(medGame1, aes(x = action, y = count/sum(count)))+
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity', fill = 'limegreen')+
    labs(title = 'Action distribution for games between 6 and 9 rounds', x = 'Action', y = 'Proportion of all actions')+
  theme_light()

medGame2 <- golfAnalysis |>
  filter(numRounds >= 10 & numRounds <= 15) |>
    pivot_longer(
    cols = c(deckPickupDiscard, deckPickupSwap, discardPickupSwap),
    names_to = 'action',
    values_to = 'count')

ggplot(medGame2, aes(x = action, y = count/sum(count))) +
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity', fill = 'lightgreen') +
  labs(title = 'Action distribution for games between 10 and 15 rounds', x = 'Action', y = 'Proportion of all actions')+
  theme_light()

It is clear that the distribution of our actions change depending on the number of hands in the game. How about the sum of our initial cards?

lowSum <- golfAnalysis |>
  filter(agentInitialSums <= 18) |>
  pivot_longer(
    cols = c(deckPickupDiscard, deckPickupSwap, discardPickupSwap),
    names_to = 'action',
    values_to = 'count')

ggplot(lowSum, aes(x = action, y = count/sum(count))) +
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity', fill = 'red')+
  labs(title = 'Action distribution when inital sum <= 18 (1st Quartile)', x = 'Action', y = 'Proportion of all actions')+
  theme_light()

medSum <- golfAnalysis |>
  filter(agentInitialSums > 18 & agentInitialSums < 27) |>
  pivot_longer(
    cols = c(deckPickupDiscard, deckPickupSwap, discardPickupSwap),
    names_to = 'action',
    values_to = 'count')

ggplot(medSum, aes(x = action, y = count/sum(count))) +
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity', fill = 'darkred')+
  labs(title = 'Action distribution when inital sum is between 18 and 27 (2nd and 3rd Quartile)', x = 'Action', y = 'Proportion of all actions')+
  theme_light()

highSum <- golfAnalysis |>
  filter(agentInitialSums >= 27) |>
  pivot_longer(
    cols = c(deckPickupDiscard, deckPickupSwap, discardPickupSwap),
    names_to = 'action',
    values_to = 'count')

ggplot(highSum, aes(x = action, y = count/sum(count))) +
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity', fill = 'firebrick3')+
  labs(title = 'Action distribution when inital sum >= 27 (4th Quartile)', x = 'Action', y = 'Proportion of all actions')+
  theme_light()

Doesn’t look like we need to condition on the sum of the initial cards. The action distribution is the same regardless what values we draw from our initial sums normal distribution.
